''See also [[scénario]]''
==English==
===Etymology===
Italian, from scena, ''scene'', from Latin scaena. See [[scene]]

===Noun===
'''scenario''' (''Plural:'' '''scenarii''')

# An outline of the [[plot]] of a [[dramatic]] or [[literary]] work.
# A [[screenplay]] itself, or an outline or a treatment of it.
# An outline or model of an expected or supposed sequence of events.

===Translations===
*Dutch: [[draaiboek]] ''n''
*Finnish: [[skenaario]]
*German: [[Drehbuch]]
*Swedish: scenario ''n''

